</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>104 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 3:31 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Getting tired of hitting that sense heading button every time it comes up so that you can tell where you're going, use this macro and save a little bit of frustration.<br><br>Assign Sense Heading to Ability Slot 1<br><br>Create a Social Macro called "Sense"<br><br>/doability 1<br>/pause 16<br>/doability 1<br>/pause 16<br>/doability 1<br><br>This will perform 3 sense headings, 1 right after the other.<br><br>Word of Warning : Don't try to type while the macro is running, because it will erase whatever is on the line when the ability triggers after the pause.&nbsp;&nbsp;And /pause 16 doability 1 doesn't seem to trigger the skill.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99237181885796></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99237181885796><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99237181885796>Help a newbie</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99237181885796#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 2:50 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a Level 3 Mage (High Elf) and need some info... I keep reading stuff about people training and specializing, etc... when people say training do they mean what shows up as "practice" on the game?&nbsp;&nbsp;And what is with this specializing business, can someone elaborate on that a little?<br><br>Thanks for any help...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99237310384631></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99237310384631><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99237310384631>RE: Help a newbie</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99237310384631#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>389 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 3:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>yes, when someone means training they mean what shows up as "practice" in the game. Specializing is what pure casters can do at level 20. You put your practice points into your specialization fields, and you get better at that area of casting. Specialization lowers the casting cost of spells in that specialized area and also makes you fizzle less. You can train one area of specialization up to 200(evocation for example) and the rest only up to 50. Whichever area hits 51 first is the one that you can take to 200. If you mess up you can do a quest to change your specialization.<br><br>Former Addict of Everquest.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

