<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99237228385927></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99237228385927><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99237228385927>RE: help please</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99237228385927#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 2:58 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am currently 30 and planning on going to Najena to work on Focus Items.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have done the broom to date. I may go to Oasis for gitants/spectres maybe, or Iceclad.  <br><br>As far as what to do at level 28, this is what I did.  I spent my time in Ill Omen, with a few odd hours here in there in FM trying for loot (the xp is lousy there in my opinion).  I did about a 50/50 split of group playing and soloing.  Soloing was easier once I hit 29, and I used the 29 Air Pet (once I got it--research is terrible and I had only earth blob from 24-29) mostly because of his stun and invisibility.  <br><br>I tried to stick to goblins and sarnaks as they drop better coin. Skeletons resist a lot it seems, and grimalkins hit hard. I pulled with Malise of course.  My other spells were see invisible to keep track of pet, burnout/burnout II, Damage shield by level, shock of blades, shock of spikes, rain of spikes, and gate (always a must in slot 8).  Just buff yourself as needed; I never keep these spells memorized.  Also note that this was my line up of spells soloing and in group.  <br><br>If you don't know already, you will be a big hit in groups if you keeps a DS on the tanks, predominantly the puller.  Our DSs are the best in the game.  In groups, I send pet (assist keying puller of course), malise, damage shield, and nuke as needed.  <br><br>I don't want to lecture because I am sure most of you know this, but I still see many mages that never practiced bind wounds.  If you haven't, do so now.  It is great for soloing as mana will always beat HP in regen it seems, even at level 30, and the bandages are free.  Also you can bandage group members up to half after battle if needed to save the healer some mana and down-time.  Just my two cents.  Good luck to all my fellow mages.  And remember "Gotta have Pet control."<br><br>Copperrfield <br>Mith Marr<br><br>P.S. In Ill Omen solo near the coast so you can fish to pass the time while you med.  I also summon a staff of warding when soloing so I can see further for best pulls.  Oh and I apologize for what is in this post that you already knew, but hopefully it will help at least 1 person out there. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
