	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, you're off to a good start choosing a gnome as your int based caster.&nbsp;&nbsp;Their innate attributes make them an excellent choice.  My advice would be to try each one to at least level 4 (when the mage gets pets) and decide which you enjoy playing the most.  <br><br>Here's something to keep in mind.  While wizards cause awe inspiring amounts of damage with their nukes at higher levels they can seem very weak and be frustrating to play at lower levels.  One must be able to deal with delayed gratification.  This is also not a great solo class.  Do you prefer to group or solo?  On the flip side, mages don't have many spells people will pay for (unlike wizard port spells).  Not having played a necromancer I can't speak for them, but I believe they can locate corpses or revive dead people for income (not to mention all their other abilities).<br><br>It really boils down to a matter of preference.  Each class has its' own charms and frustrations.  The question is which combination of those can you most easily live with?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
